Accounts.Name: Sales
Accounts.Description: Income from any normal business activity

Accounts.Name: Other Revenue
Accounts.Description: Any other income that does not relate to  normal business activity and is not recurring

Accounts.Name: Interest Income
Accounts.Description: Gross interest income

Accounts.Name: Cost of Goods Sold
Accounts.Description: Cost of goods sold by the business

Accounts.Name: Direct Wages
Accounts.Description: Payment of wages/salary to an employee whose work can be directly linked to the product or service

Accounts.Name: Direct Expenses
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred that relate directly to earning revenue

Accounts.Name: Advertising & Marketing
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred for advertising and marketing

Accounts.Name: Audit & Accountancy fees
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred relating to accounting and audit fees

Accounts.Name: Bank Fees
Accounts.Description: Fees charged by your bank for transactions regarding your bank account(s)

Accounts.Name: Cleaning
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred for cleaning business property

Accounts.Name: Consulting
Accounts.Description: Payments made to consultants

Accounts.Name: Depreciation Expense
Accounts.Description: The amount of the asset's cost (based on the useful life) that was consumed during the period

Accounts.Name: Charitable and Political Donations
Accounts.Description: Payments made to charities or political organisations or events

Accounts.Name: Entertainment-100% business
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on entertainment by the business that for income tax purposes are fully deductable

Accounts.Name: Entertainment - 0%
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on entertainment by the business that for income tax purposes are not fully deductable

Accounts.Name: Postage, Freight & Courier
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred by the entity on postage, freight & courier costs

Accounts.Name: General Expenses
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred that relate to the general running of the business

Accounts.Name: Insurance
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred for insuring the business' assets

Accounts.Name: Interest Paid
Accounts.Description: Interest paid on a business bank account or credit card account

Accounts.Name: Legal Expenses
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on any legal matters

Accounts.Name: Light, Power, Heating
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred for lighting, power or heating the business premises

Accounts.Name: Motor Vehicle Expenses
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on the running of business motor vehicles

Accounts.Name: Operating Lease Payments
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on operating expenses such as office rental and vehicle leases (excludes hire purchase agreements)

Accounts.Name: Printing & Stationery
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on printing and stationery

Accounts.Name: IT Software and Consumables
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred  on  software or computer consumables

Accounts.Name: Rates
Accounts.Description: Payments made to local council for rates

Accounts.Name: Rent
Accounts.Description: Payments  made to lease a building or area

Accounts.Name: Repairs & Maintenance
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on a damaged or run down asset that will bring the asset back to its original condition

Accounts.Name: Salaries
Accounts.Description: Payment to employees in exchange for their resources

Accounts.Name: Directors' Remuneration
Accounts.Description: Payments to company directors in exchange for their resources

Accounts.Name: Employers National Insurance
Accounts.Description: Payment made for National Insurance contributions - business contribution only

Accounts.Name: Staff Training
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred in relation to training staff

Accounts.Name: Pensions Costs
Accounts.Description: Payments made to pension schemes

Accounts.Name: Medical Insurance
Accounts.Description: Payments made to medical insurance schemes

Accounts.Name: Subscriptions
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred by the business in relation to subscriptions, such as magazines and professional bodies

Accounts.Name: Telephone & Internet
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred from any business-related phone calls, phone lines, or internet connections

Accounts.Name: Travel - National
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred from any domestic business travel

Accounts.Name: Travel - International
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred from any international business travel

Accounts.Name: Bank Revaluations
Accounts.Description: Bank account revaluations due for foreign exchange rate changes

Accounts.Name: Unrealised Currency Gains
Accounts.Description: Unrealised currency gains on outstanding items

Accounts.Name: Realised Currency Gains
Accounts.Description: Gains or losses made due to currency exchange rate changes

Accounts.Name: Corporation Tax
Accounts.Description: Tax payable on business profits

Accounts.Name: Accounts Receivable
Accounts.Description: Invoices the business has issued but has not yet collected payment on

Accounts.Name: Less Provision for Doubtful Debts
Accounts.Description: A provision anticipating that a portion of accounts receivable will never be collected

Accounts.Name: Prepayments
Accounts.Description: An expenditure that has been paid for in advance

Accounts.Name: Inventory
Accounts.Description: Value of tracked items for resale.

Accounts.Name: Office Equipment
Accounts.Description: Office equipment that is owned and controlled by the business

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Office Equipment
Accounts.Description: The total amount of office equipment costs that has been consumed by the business (based on the useful life)

Accounts.Name: Computer Equipment
Accounts.Description: Computer equipment that is owned and controlled by the business

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Computer Equipment
Accounts.Description: The total amount of computer equipment costs that has been consumed by the business (based on the useful life)

Accounts.Name: Buildings
Accounts.Description: Buildings that are owned and controlled by the business

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Buildings
Accounts.Description: The total amount of buildings costs that have been consumed by the business (based on the useful life)

Accounts.Name: Leasehold Improvements
Accounts.Description: The value added to the leased premises via improvements

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Leasehold Improvements
Accounts.Description: The total amount of leasehold improvement costs that has been consumed by the business (based on the useful life)

Accounts.Name: Motor Vehicles
Accounts.Description: Motor vehicles that are owned and controlled by the business

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Motor Vehicles
Accounts.Description: The total amount of motor vehicle costs that has been consumed by the business (based on the useful life)

Accounts.Name: Plant and Machinery
Accounts.Description: Plant and machinery that are owned and controlled by the business

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Plant and Machinery
Accounts.Description: The total amount of plant and machinery cost that has been consumed by the business (based on the useful life)

Accounts.Name: Intangibles
Accounts.Description: Assets with no physical presence e.g. goodwill or patents

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Amortisation on Intangibles
Accounts.Description: The total amount of intangibles that have been consumed by the business

Accounts.Name: Accounts Payable
Accounts.Description: Invoices the company has received from suppliers but have not made payment on

Accounts.Name: Unpaid Expense Claims
Accounts.Description: Expense claims typically made by employees/shareholder employees which the business has not made payment on

Accounts.Name: Wages Payable
Accounts.Description: Xero automatically updates this account for payroll entries created using Payroll and will store the payroll amount to be paid to the employee for the pay run. This account enables you to maintain separate accounts for employee Wages Payable amounts and Accounts Payable amounts

Accounts.Name: Accruals
Accounts.Description: Any services the business has received but have not yet been invoiced for e.g. Accountancy Fees

Accounts.Name: Income in Advance
Accounts.Description: Any income the business has received but have not provided the goods or services for

Accounts.Name: Credit Card Control Account
Accounts.Description: The amount owing on the company's credit cards

Accounts.Name: Wages Payable - Payroll
Accounts.Description: Where this account is set as the nominated Wages Payable account within Payroll Settings, Xero allocates the net wage amount of each pay run created using Payroll to this account

Accounts.Name: Employee contribution to benefits
Accounts.Description: Payroll deductions for employee contributions towards payrolled benefits in kind

Accounts.Name: VAT
Accounts.Description: The balance in this account represents VAT owing to or from the HMRC. At the end of the VAT period, it is this account that should be used to code against either the ‘refunds from’ or ‘payments to’ the HMRC that will appear on the bank statement. Xero has been designed to use only one VAT account to track VAT on income and expenses, so there is no need to add any new VAT accounts to Xero

Accounts.Name: PAYE Payable
Accounts.Description: The Amount of PAYE tax due to be paid to the HMRC

Accounts.Name: NIC Payable
Accounts.Description: The amount of a business' portion of National Insurance Contribution that is due to be paid to the HMRC

Accounts.Name: Provision for Corporation Tax
Accounts.Description: Corporation tax payable to the HMRC

Accounts.Name: Directors' Loan Account
Accounts.Description: Monies owed to or from company directors

Accounts.Name: Historical Adjustment
Accounts.Description: For any accounting and starting balance adjustments

Accounts.Name: Suspense
Accounts.Description: A clearing account

Accounts.Name: Pensions Payable
Accounts.Description: Payroll pension payable account

Accounts.Name: Rounding
Accounts.Description: An adjustment entry to allow for rounding

Accounts.Name: Earnings Orders Payable
Accounts.Description: Payroll earnings order account

Accounts.Name: Tracking Transfers
Accounts.Description: Transfers between tracking categories

Accounts.Name: Loan
Accounts.Description: Any money that has been borrowed from a creditor

Accounts.Name: Hire Purchase Loan
Accounts.Description: Any goods bought through hire purchase agreements

Accounts.Name: Deferred Tax
Accounts.Description: Used if there is a timing difference between taxable profits and accounting profits

Accounts.Name: Student Loan Deductions Payable
Accounts.Description: Payroll student loan deductions payable account

Accounts.Name: Capital - x,xxx Ordinary Shares
Accounts.Description: Paid up capital

Accounts.Name: Retained Earnings
Accounts.Description: Do not Use

Accounts.Name: Owner A Funds Introduced
Accounts.Description: Funds contributed by the owner

Accounts.Name: Owner A Drawings
Accounts.Description: Withdrawals by the owners
